{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 What all did we get? Well, nothing too surprising, and let me explain why.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The ideas that we hold to be true without proof comprise our {\i doxa}. That is, the things we assume to be true, or to be the case, without needing to have anything backing those assumptions up. When one looks around the furry fandom at time of writing, one is likely to find a subculture made up mostly of men.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 To that, the survey offers only confirmation. A bit more than 75% of the respondents \u8212- certainly a supermajority \u8212- responded that their gender identity was masculine or mostly masculine. Although one\u8217's expression or presentation used as a predictor has its flaws, a glance around the average convention space bears truth to this claim: we can mark that down as one point for doxa reading things correctly.\par}
