{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Now, how about we look at gender alignment; that is, let\u8217's take a look at the breakdown of how folks\u8217' gender identity aligns with their sex as assigned at birth. For example, a trans man who was assigned female at birth, but identifies as a man now, would be someone who would fall under the umbrella term of \u8216'transgender\u8217', while a man who was assigned male at birth would fall under the term \u8216'cisgender\u8217'. Additionally, for the sake of completeness, the survey also offered the choice for the respondent to answer that the answer was more complicated than these two choices would allow (we did not ask for further details, and had we, we would not be able to share them while preserving anonymity, of course).\par}
